column3: Global surface temperature change relative to 1850-1900 from observations and CMIP6 models (human, human&natural, aerosol and natural forcings simulations)

Data is for the black, blue, red, grey and green lines as well as blue, red, grey and green shadings in FAQ3.1 Figure 1 in the IPCC Working Group I Contribution to the Sixth Assessment Report: Chapter 3
Global Surface Temperature Anomalies (GSTA) is computed from CMIP6 models ensemble (hist-GHG, historical-ssp245, hist-aer and hist-nat experiments) and HadCRUT4.6 observations
